Here lies the body of Mary Lee;
She bore five sons and one daughter;
She died at twenty-five, of a disorder brought on
By the birth of her last child, and the death of her husband.

Here lies the body of Mary Lee;
She was a kind and loving mother;
She never complained, though life was unkind,
And her heart was buried with her husband.

Here lies the body of Mary Lee;
Her children mourn her loss each day;
They know she's in a better place, but still they wish
She could have stayed a little longer.

Here lies Mary Lee, at peace at last;
Her trials and tribulations are past;
She left a legacy of love and courage,
And her memory will forever be cherished.
